HEADWORD: Palo blanco
<hw>Pa"lo blan"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Sp. <ets>blanco</ets>
white.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A western American hackberry
(<spn>Celtis reticulata</spn>), having light-colored bark.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A Mexican mimosaceous tree (<spn>Lysiloma
candida</spn>), the bark of which is used in tanning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

